<paragraph blockId="6.[264,665,1332,1393]" box="[264,393,1367,1393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,384,1367,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–7" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1161,1185]" captionTargetBox="[310,1273,401,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-309@7.[290,1297,386,1140]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–7. Chrysosoma shixingense sp. nov. (Male). 6. Left It1, right lateral view; 7. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050275/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Figs. 6–7</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1320,1447,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis. Antenna black; frons with 1 long pale curved hair on postero­lateral slope; coxae black; FI with row of long pale spine­like ventral bristles (the longest bristles 4 times as long as width of FI).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1320,1447,1873]" box="[312,1126,1567,1593]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Description. Male body length 4.4–5.0 mm, wing length 4.8–5.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1320,1447,1873]" lastBlockId="7.[264,1322,284,350]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; vertex distinctly excavated, frons subshining. Hairs and bristles on head black; middle and lower postocular bristles (including postero­ventral hairs) pale; frons with 1 long and 1 short strong pvt and 1 long pale curved hair on postero­lateral slope, ocellar tubercle with 2 long strong oc and 2 rather short bristles. Antenna black; scape somewhat swollen; pedicel with circlet of apical bristles (including 1 long thick dorsal and 1 long thick ventral bristles, the ventral much longer than the dorsal); first flagellomere subconical, 2.2 times longer than wide; arista apical, blackish, simple, 1.2 times longer than head + thorax. Proboscis brown with blackish hairs; palpus blackish with pale hairs and 2 black bristles.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050275" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5050275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050275/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" startId="7.[264,382,1161,1185]" targetBox="[310,1273,401,1131]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1322,1160,1226]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,437,1160,1186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">FIGURES 6–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhu &amp; Yang, 2005" authorityName="Zhu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2005" box="[444,707,1162,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shixingense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[444,707,1162,1185]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Chrysosoma shixingense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,797,1162,1185]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Male). 6. Left It 
<subScript attach="left" box="[981,988,1176,1189]" fontSize="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">1</subScript>
, right lateral view; 7. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,1282,1876]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on thorax black; 2 strong posterior dc and 4 anterior hairs; 5–6 long irregularly paired acr; scutellum with 2 pairs of sc, basal pair short and weak. Legs black; coxae and trochanters black; apices of femora, bases and apices of tibiae, and t 
<subScript attach="left" box="[744,765,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">2­5</subScript>
brownish, t 
<subScript attach="left" box="[908,916,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">1</subScript>
dark yellow. Hairs and bristles on legs black; coxae with pale lateral hairs. Femora with long pale ventral hairs: FI with row of long pale spine­like ventral bristles (the longest bristles 4 times as long as width of FI); FII with row of long hair­like pale av and pv (2 times longer as long as width of FII); FIII with row of long hair­like pale av and pv (nearly as long as width of FIII). TI with 3–4 ad and 1pv at apical 1/5, apically with 2 long and 1 short bristles; TII with 3 ad, apically with 1 bristles; TIII with 1 ad at basal 1/5, 2 pd, and 5–6 pv, apically with 2 bristles. It 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1234,1242,1660,1674]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">1</subScript>
somewhat flattened with very short dense ventral pubescence from basal 1/6 to 2/3 (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1250,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–7" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1161,1185]" captionTargetBox="[310,1273,401,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-309@7.[290,1297,386,1140]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–7. Chrysosoma shixingense sp. nov. (Male). 6. Left It1, right lateral view; 7. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050275/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Relative lengths of tibia and tarsomeres: LI 2.5: 2.2: 0.7: 0.5: 0.3: 0.2; LII 4.6: 3.6: 1.0: 0.7: 0.4: 0.2; LIII 6.8: 3.0: 1.2: 0.7: 0.5: 0.2. Wing: hyaline, tinged with brown; veins dark brown, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[382,390,1824,1838]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">1</subScript>
concave, crossvein m­cu straight. Squama dark yellow, margin blackish with pale hairs. Halter yellow with pale knob.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Abdomen dark metallic green with gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on abdomen black, but sterna 1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[401,414,325,349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">–</emphasis>
3 with long pale hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[504,579,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–7" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1161,1185]" captionTargetBox="[310,1273,401,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-309@7.[290,1297,386,1140]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–7. Chrysosoma shixingense sp. nov. (Male). 6. Left It1, right lateral view; 7. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050275/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
): Epandrium distinctly much longer than wide with 3 lateral hairs; surstylus rather thick, apically with some weak bristles and basally with a short finger­like lateral process; hypandrium with narrow left lateral arm, nearly reaching apex of aedeagus; aedeagus bent; cercus furcated apically, with black bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,950]" box="[312,536,524,550]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
